<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06090102 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06090102 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photos (2); PHOTO: Agee; PHOTO: Martin  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  RELIGION; LIFESTYLE; ORGANIZATION; US; MEETING; SANTA-CLARA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  More than 1,500 delegates from California and around the world will conveneWednesday through April 7 at the Santa Clara Marriott Hotel for the tenthannual Human Life International Conference on Love, Life and the Family.;    ACatholic organization based in Gaithersburg, Md., Human Life Internationalopposes abortion and promotes family values, said local spokesman Arthur Brew.Brew said about one-third of those expected to attend are not Catholic.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Religion andamp; Ethics  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  CATHOLIC ORGANIZATION EXPECTS 1,500 AT SANTACLARA MEETINGHUMAN LIFE CONFERENCE TARGETS SOCIAL ISSUES  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     More than 60 experts will discuss AIDS, abortion, euthanasia andpornography. Among them are Dr. Bernard Nathanson, a fetologist who producedthe controversial anti-abortion film &quot;The Silent Scream&quot;; James Likoudis,president of Catholics United for the Faith; chastity experts Coleen Nast andBarbara McGuigan and Mary Cunningham Agee, former Bendix Corp. executive, nowhead of the Nurturing Network, a support system offering alternatives toabortion for pregnant women.;    The conference includes a special HispanicCongress, with talks by Spanish-speaking experts from the United States andLatin America.;    Also on the conference agenda, Brew said, is the launchingof &quot;Operation White Rose,&quot; a national movement to counter right-to-die groupsin the United States. The movement takes its name from the white rose that agroup of German medical students chose during World War II as a symbol forprotesting Hitler's euthanasia and genocide projects. The students wereultimately executed.;    San Jose Bishop Pierre DuMaine will open theconference at 7 p.m. Wednesday with a Mass and rosary at Our Lady of PeaceChurch, adjacent to the conference site. Keynote speaker at a 7 p.m. dinnerApril 7 is conservative theologian Malachi Martin, an expert on Vaticanaffairs.; IFYOU'RE INTERESTED; For information about the conference, call(415) 969-8977.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff Report  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910330  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  9C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  287  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday March 30, 199100090102,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>